 falls in love with a Muslim holy man, and goddesses rub shoulders with kings and merchants. Across religion, class, and gender, what binds these fabulous stories together is the characters’ pursuit of living honorably and morally in a difficult, corrupt world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aBengali (South Asian people)xFolklore. 0aTaleszIndiazBengal. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aHindu heroes.  aadventure.  acaste system.  aeconomic class.  alove.  amythological.  amyths.  aordinary people.  apremodern.  aredemption.  asocial differences.  asouth asian stories.  astruggle.  asurvival.  atales from Bengal.  atranslated works.  aworld literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520388949?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520388949423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520388949/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY